From Richard Sturges Subject Re Help me adjust my tappits In Matthew Sheppard writes All our local 'experts' say it's the tappits that need some adjusting so I am soon to attempt I would like any advice anyone I do not have a shop manual but have read about the procedure in Chiltons and in a few other Is there anything I need to be particularaly carful of Any problems anyone else has encountered I would stongly recommend a factory service manual and if you are not an experienced machanic then get a chiltons or haynes sp Make sure the bike has cooled at least hours since being Read the books and if you have more questions you could mail Also be very careful when tightening valve cover They take very little torque and breaking one is Rich Sturges Falls Church VA